# Before any edit in mxdb-sync

1. **Read** `agent.md` at the repository root (sync architecture, design principles, test pointers).
2. **Read** `c:/code/personal/agents/global-agent.md` when `agent.md` points to it (or when making non-trivial changes).

Do **not** start implementing code changes until these have been read for the current task (skim is fine for tiny typo-only fixes if the user says so).

If a file is missing or unreadable, say so and proceed only with what the user confirms.
